 Sixthly, after Proceſſe by Attachments or diſtreſſes, once
Or diſtreſſes. granted the Sheriff ex officio may grant new Proceſſe of the ſame nature. And ſo after judgement entred he may grant out execution of courſe, if the Court do not ſtay it. But otherwiſe theſe officers are not to doe any thing without the Benchers, except in caſe of neceſſity, as granting of Replevins;
                     Replevins. this is done of courſe.
